# qodana-cpp — Qodana for C/C++ / CLion (image name = repoName). Feed code QDCPP. Internal nightly dist
# feed: unsigned tar.gz, sha256-only (no GPG .asc), eap (the nightly feed is eap-only); the build
# mounts QODANA_READ_SPACE_PACKAGES_TOKEN (compose.private.yaml).
# Distinct from the Community qodana-clang (feed code QDCL, clang-tidy TOOL, no IDE dist): cpp ships the
# full CLion IDE dist and uses the standard `qodana` CLI (CLI_BINARY=qodana, Cli kind).
#
# Builds on the SHARED trixie debian-base (the same QD_TRIXIE_BASE_IMAGE as jvm-community/python/rust/
# dotnet), which ships NO clang, so it REUSES lib/toolchain/clang.dockerfile (FROM base AS
# clang-toolchain — the LLVM apt repo pinned by CLANG/CLANG_OS) — the SAME fragment qodana-clang uses —
# then the in-place node (NODE_MAJOR) + eslint fragments append onto clang-toolchain (CLion analyzes
# JS/TS). SINGLE build cell CLANG=20/CLANG_OS=trixie (the trixie LLVM repo row in clang-versions.txt; the
# multi-clang tag matrix is deferred with qodana-clang's, single-tag today).
#
# CLion scans shell out to sudo (source PRIVILEGED=true), so cpp INCLUDEs lib/privileged.dockerfile and
# its dist FROMs the privileged stage. Since node+eslint append onto clang-toolchain, privileged FROMs
# clang-toolchain via base.dockerfile's GLOBAL DEFAULT PRIVILEGED_BASE_STAGE — so cpp sets NO
# PRIVILEGED_BASE_STAGE override (the qodana-clang convention), unlike ruby/dotnet whose node+eslint sit
# on base. DIST_BASE_STAGE=privileged is an .env KEY (base.dockerfile does NOT default DIST_BASE_STAGE,
# so the INCLUDE_ARGS value survives to `FROM ${DIST_BASE_STAGE:-base} AS dist` — the android/php/ruby/
# dotnet convention). The dockerfile sets CXX/CC/CPLUS_INCLUDE_PATH cpp-locally (the source
# cpp.Dockerfile exports them so CLion's analysis resolves the LLVM compiler), parameterized on CLANG.
#
# uid 1000 is FREE on the trixie base, so default 1000, NO uid keys (the source uses 1001; lib/base
# creates the qodana user at the free 1000 — the rust/ruby/dotnet divergence, phase-0). eslint is pinned
# in lib/toolchain/eslint/package.json (renovate). Pins live in docs/phase-0-decisions.md;
# CppEnvContractTest asserts byte-identity for the dist pins + the trixie base digest. Key set = jvm's
# key set + DIST_BASE_STAGE + CLANG + CLANG_OS.
QD_LINTER_SLUG=qodana-cpp
QD_VERSION=2026.3
QD_BUILD=263.130.1007
QD_DISTRIBUTION_FEED=https://packages.jetbrains.team/files/p/sa/qodana-dist-internal/feed
QD_VERIFY_MODE=sha256
QD_PRODUCT_INFO_CODE=CL
QD_BASE_IMAGE=dhi.io/debian-base:trixie-debian13-dev@sha256:68b5f4c2c789b99dc6ab7574c7e695e724646f64616619c48c3245f8aaeae459
DIST_BASE_STAGE=privileged
CLANG=20
CLANG_OS=trixie
CLI_BINARY=qodana
CLI_VERSION=2026.2
CLI_OS=linux
NODE_MAJOR=20
